reviews.text: This is a great resource for the community and for visitors. I was born & raised in Columbus & truly value Experience Columbus' impact to our city. You can pick up awesome information about all the latest happenings around town all year long.
As always, helpful staff. I always buy my AirConnect bus ticket here. $2.75 for one way trip to/from airport to downtown & Convention Center.
Always a great place to visit.i enjoy going in there
This is a great place for anyone who is coming in from out of Columbus, and need ideas to know what to do in the Columbus area.
Was there to collect our ale trail glasses but the man wasn't the most friendly. The place was good for tourist though.

Whole Foods always has good customer service the employees are always willing to answer any questions you have. Yesterday I was at the one at Carlisle I could actually make a day of it. They have so much to choose from and their deli are definitely to die for. The only one thing is I wish the prices were a little lower. The bakery is also very good. 👍👍👍🤔and the thought full sign is hoping they will drop their prices a bit.

Stopped here while traveling to visit family. Bought from the salad bar and the best organic cherry tomatoes for my son. Very nice store and was busy. Surprised by the mention of Amazon prime memberships at the register when paying them

The quality of food here is plummeting. I have found dirt in my ground beef twice now: two weeks in a row. Recently we found plastic in the clam chowder. Its not really what I would expect from Whole foods. I would like to continue shopping here but I am a little worried.

I only come here for the unhealthy food or when I really want some good meat or cheese. I don't give a hoot about the healthy organic all natural buzzword food. Personally, it's overrated, overpriced, and not worth it. But that bakery? I will eat all 1000 calories of that tiny little cake. No regrets. 
Good selection of cheese, great place for fresh meat and local coffee. 

Also, there seems to be bar soap everywhere. Really.. it seemed every 2-3 aisles there was a display for some sort of soap. So much so that I'm beginning to think that this Whole Foods location is trying to tell us we smell bad. Well jokes on you Whole Foods! I showered at least twice since I last visited 3 months ago! 

Generally very friendly staff though! Even if they think we smell bad..
Can I get a smile from anyone in this place? Healthy living what about been good to one another.  $ changes people.  #compassion #bekind #smile

SEVEN WORDS: SALTINE CRUSTED, GREASY PEPPERONI, SALTY MOZZARELLA GOODNESS.

I usually get odd pizzas here - olives/sausage/mushrooms, or whatever my co-pilot wants.

This time, it was  first trip for my nephew, and we .usually decided on a simple large pepperoni pizza.

What a great choice! It tasted just about perfect! One of the best straight-forward pizzas I've ever had. 

Additionally, the "pizzeria" ambience is quite fine, too. No frills, just good dining.

However, there are two big drawbacks to "no frills": Rubinos is Cash Only + No Beef/Hamburger topping.

What? This is an affluent Jewish neighborhood near a large, diverse college. That being said,  Rubinos falls far short of 5-stars. I'd give if 3 stars if the pizza wasn't so fantastic today.

Quite busy but pizza is great. Although definitely think that it's worth mentioning that they only accept cash for pizza. Or anything really I did not know this and I had to go to the ATM to get cash to pick up my pizza so I think everyone should know before that they go that they only accept cash.
A fav location for tasty Pizza. Service is always prompt even when they have a full house. This place has an awesome feel to it.
Very old school! Great pizza, great service! CASH ONLY. They do not accept credit card but great for a planned afternoon. Would recommend for a casual lunch or dinner.

When I think of Ohio pizza, Rubino's is the best hands down!  This staple of Bexley is without a doubt my favorite pizza.  It's thin crust perfection severed up in a paper tent.  It was my favorite spot to eat as a kid and was always one of the first stops when I would come back to town.  From the pinball machine to the cash only policy, the place has always felt like home to me.  It's a cool place to eat in at for lunch or pick up and take home for dinner.  They keep everything nice and hot for pickup.  Make sure you order plenty because I crush a pepperoni pizza by myself.  It's too good to stop at a few slices!  Don't sleep on the house salad, it's amazing.

I want to like this place, I really do, and I guess I do like it. However, one thing baffles me - whether you order a three or four piece meal, you get the same amount of Cane's sauce. I like their sauce, but wish there were options, but why is the same amount of sauce offered regardless of how much tasty chicken is ordered?

Nice design inside, ....not the standard floor plan in used to for Canes.  Clean, food good,  what I've come to know as Canes, maybe better, as the chicken was not over-cooked.  Canes location with a good dining experience (sat and ate with one of my daughters).

I loved it till I found a bone in my chicken tender!!!!! But when I took it into the store they did give me another complete order!!!!! My husband was sort excited about the whole situation because he got 3 meals outta it I couldn't eat anymore once I got the bone but besides that service was excellent and the service was great!!!!!!!!
Good food.  Staff is kind.  Had good consistancy.  Slightly difficult to get out of.

Food, great as always. However there seems to be a lack of training when it comes to paying with a gift card. If there's a problem with the gift card, and you think you should get the managers help,  why ask the customer if that's what you should do? You're the employee, you decide.
Lemonade was good but they make their chicken salad with miracle whip so I was not a fan.
Food was made wrong tables were dirty the help was ok
Over priced and most of the sandwiches aren't good.  The customer service was great.
I love going to Penn Station the food is always fresh and wonderful and I've always been satisfied
Fast service, great subs and always fresh fries!

Love this place, no complaints. It's fun mixing and matching sauces. None of the meat we ordered was dry at all, which was a nice little surprise! Bit pricey, so I can't come here too often. I think my favorite was the pulled pork. Nice cozy interior, rustic feel.

This is a review of the Upper Arlington location for 4/10/19 at 4:20pm. The two women in the front need to work on their customer service skills. We arrived to pick up an online order. We stood at the registered with two female employees standing at the food window.....while they were getting another order together, neither bothered to even acknowledge us or say "we will be right with you". After 5 minutes they finally asked what we needed. Then as we were checking the order and mentioned that we were not sure everything was correct, the one stated, "it's all their" in a condescending tone.

Great BBQ but the menu is confusing when trying to place an order. I realize that they are playing to the customers that are repeat and know the operation but it is very hard for a newbie to make a decision when ordering their meal up front. Good example is the difference between a lunch sandwich and a regular.
With almost 1000 reviews they have to be doing something right. Great food, outstanding atmosphere. Employees are always great to customers. 5 stars all day!
It's okay. Decent BBQ, sauces are good. Service is poor. Good for a BBQ fix, but not for anybody serious about their cue
I liked the place. The amount of food they give us good. I tried fish, which was good. Very friendly staff. A lot of people just take away. So, it's not very crowded usually.
One of my favorite spots for tasty chinese food. Everyone at our table was glad to be there. Looking forward to a return trip. Food is similar to a place in San Francisco I liked.

I started coming here pretty regularly about 3 years ago, I think. My first dish was the curry chicken, I believe, and then I moved on to some of the other dishes on the menu. I really like the spicy beef noodle soup, and the spicy chicken wings. I also recommend the pork dish with spicy sauce (I forget the exact name). The Singapore rice noodles is another favorite, too. I'm glad I started coming here, because I miss the No 1 Chinese restaurant that used to be on High St (Rippers, then some other place moved into that space).

Yau' s Chinese Bistro offers a tasty affordable meal. What stood out the most was how quick the food was served. I was there with my family and all of us ordered different dishes and we all got our food almost at once!

I ordered their food from Postmates. I ordered the egg drop soup, fried chicken, fried rice, and an eggroll. It tasted really good!!! This is my first time eating REAL Chinese food in Ohio. I used to frequent a Chinese restaurant in New Jersey and felt like they had the best food. Especially the gravy and white rice. I love the food here and will definitely come back!

Always great food and friendly service. I appreciate their selection of specials and that they seem to actually put some effort into inspired eats and drinks. If you're waiting for a table do not despair they are surprisingly adapt to moving people in and out of their dining room.

Really enjoyed my time at Mimi's! Had the salmon dinner. I order it everytime and it is always amazing. Sign up for their emails and they will send you a coupon each month for a buy one get one free entree as long as you buy two non alcoholic drinks with your entrees. Great family restaurant!
If I could give more that a 5 star I would.  This was my first time being at Mimi's and I will go back again very soon.  Food was delicious and the service was wonderful

My first visit here. To start we ordered a cinnamon roll. It was hard as a rock. My mimosa was really good but we thought we were getting brunch special. It was sold to us at regular price. Lack of communication from our server. My salmon Benedict was good except my egg was way overcooked, and the hollandaise was broken. Our server was not pleasant to deal with. Don't think we will go back.
Great staff, great food, kid friendly. I liked my jambalaya, though it didn't have much heat.  Overall a good time.

Love Wendy's burgers. I think they are so much better than so many of the other burger chains. Got the biggie bag for 5 dollars. It was much less than the way it looks on the ad (mini burger, 4 small nuggets, very little bacon in a sandwich that is advertised to be double stacked. Therefore 4 stars) but nevertheless I left satisfied.

I really like this Wendy's. It's one of my favorite places to grab a quick lunch. Very clean, fast and great customer service. The isn't dripping grease like a couple of other Wendy's restaurants I have been to. Definitely recommend. Also the strawberry lemonade is a must have.
Nice ,fast ,friendly got my food in and out quick good price good food  fish sandwich  2. To be exact disappeared nothing flat
Andrew runs a great day crew they take pride in food quality & customer service which i see almost 3-5 times per week. The best grilled Asiago chicken

Best coffee out of all the other local fast food places, even if they don't serve breakfast they open at 10am if you want an early burger, I recommend a Dave's Double or one of his signature burgers because they're the best!

A little hidden at the back of the parking lot, but worth looking for. You can call ahead to place an order. The food is great. You can go to a sit down restaurant and order Mexican street tacos or just buy the real thing.

The location was a little shady I will admit but how good the food was made up for that. This was the most authentic Mexican food I ever had in ohio, also their prices are reasonably cheap. They've most definitely have themselves some new regular customers.
They really are the best tacos in town (and best quesadilla I've ever had). My search is finally over! Great friendly staff is always a huge plus.
Just tried for the first time. This is going to be my new place to eat. Nice lady at checkout and very tasty food
Excellent customer service. Their food has always come out fresh, hot and delicious.

Great food. My wife is a pescetarian, had the fried shrimp and an Impossible slider which she enjoyed a great deal. I really like the double stack sliders. Consistently good at whatever location we've visited around the country. Only one question remains - when are you coming to Pittsburgh?
Nice location for what you crave! I never have to wait for long grabbing some delicious mini burgers. I've seen a little in to the kitchen and it is pretty clean. Nice place!
Fast service very friendly food good and hot main thing they got the order right.

The drive thru person (receipt says "team member #1177) is extremely friendly and made sure the order was complete and correct. He gave me napkins without asking as everyone should with drive thru orders. Thank you for being thorough.

I don't know what the fuss is all about. Good is ok but at the same time. The service was very spotty. Man at drive thru did not say thank you or even respond to my questions. It was good priced for the tiny burgers. To be honest I think the frozen ones are better than fresh!!

This place was phenomenal they have a buffet there that is so good and very authentic! we had the most entertaining guy playing the accordion for us it was something special if I can find my pictures I will definitely post a picture! oh my gosh I may have these phenomenal desserts also let me tell you the cream puffs were like gigantic and so many different flavors. Really good service too servers are so friendly and nice. The next time I'm in the Columbus area I'm definitely going to go there again! I highly recommend this place for the food, the atmosphere, and the fun!!!

The food at Schmidt's is not my favorite. I'm not a huge fan of German food in general, and I like the way Wurst und Bier serves up schnitzel, my favorite German dish, better than Schmidt's does. Still, if you are a fan of German food, or just a fan of unique, destination dining, you owe it to yourself to visit Schmidt's. This place attracts lots of tourists, but it is also a local favorite. German Village is a beautiful, historic Columbus neighborhood, and Schmidt's is a deserving anchor and part of its charm. Although most of the menu just isn't my cup of tea, one huge exception to this is the famous Schmidt's cream puff. All other cream puff pale in comparison. I've been known to hunt down one of Schmidt's food trucks visiting my neighborhood just to get a cream puff. They are so good!

We stopped here for lunch while in Columbus for an overnight stay. The food and ambiance were amazing. The sausages were flavorful and on point. The sides were excellent. The red cabbage and German potato salad were well flavored and balanced, not too sweet. My wife had a chicken dish with a basil cream sauce that was outstanding. 
You must get one of the enormous cream puffs. Perfect end to our meal. 
If ever in Columbus, this is a must for great German food.

We were recommended by locals to visit this place and was very pleased! The restaurant actually looks like something out of a Christmas village, so wonderful & quaint! Once inside, we were greeted with a large glass case of their famous cream puffs the size of softballs, along with various pastries of German chocolate cake, French silk pies and more. Although the restaurant was crowded, we were seated almost immediately. Since it was our first time there, we opted for the buffet. There were various types of German sausages, pastas, potato salads, 1 type of soup, rolls, etc. Everything we tried was exceptional! My husband & I ordered their hot buttered rum which was absolutely delicious. Service was wonderful! Overall, I can see why this place came highly recommended. Wonderful food, ambiance & service! Just sad we can't take this restaurant home with us lol

Hadn't been here in 10+ yrs, due to bad service & horrible buffet bar that day. Wanted to give it another try. Can't say it was fantastic, seeing how after we had our salads, went back to buffet for the main meal, come back to table to find it had been totally cleared off & apparently reset for new customers. Wow! Had to wait for new drinks & place settings while the food cooled.  Otherwise, food wasn't bad, but was it worth the $16 a person for buffet? Couldn't resist the pies though as take home option. But seriously, $50 (w tip) for 2 people??? The buffet isn't worth THAT much!! Another 10 yrs, me might try it again! Maybe...
The best local brewery. Not only because of the beer but because of how they manage their releases. Always a good time.
Awesome inside and out great staff
Ask them to double dip the hot wings, trust me you wont do that again!!!

Great beer and awesome up-and-coming  brewery. Don't let any negative reviews dissuade you from buying their beer!! These are all from people confused about the production facility (here) and the restaurant, which is NOT affiliated! People that show up here and write negative reviews are unjustly upset because they didn't do their research. While they are working very hard to set up a tap room, there is currently not one and this site is not open for public tours.
Awesome people brewing awesome beer!

Amazing place to brunch. They really value local ingredients. The food is always amazing. It's comfort food at it's core, but elevated with amazing ingredients. The service is great. The coffee has a paragraph long love letter about it on the menu and its delicious.

The food was terrific. Some of the best restaurant food I have tasted. Everything was fresh and delicious. Service was friendly and efficient. The prices are high based on the amount of food or I would rate a 5. Be prepared to wait. The dining area is small.
Wonderful place to visit. Delicious food and drinks. The service is always good. Beware to get there early though.. it gets busy very quickly.
Great option for breakfast. Ordered an omelette with chili, coffee and orange juice. Food tastes great. Hopefully they can expand soon, as the place is small. I recommend this one!
Excellent breakfast. Quality service, quality food, unique menu. One of my new favorite spots for a farm to table breakfast. A must try in Columbus.

How sad is it that this place closed?!?? This restaurant was spectacular and the risks Alana consistently took were a welcomed departure from the majority of the options nearby.  Please post new projects so we can support them!  We miss you and your awesome husband!

Alana's has been great both times I visited.  The space had a unique feel to it, almost like you are at someone's house.  Food is really good, everything I've tried had been great.  Probably the best steak I've had in Columbus.

I really like the idea of a "surprise" dinner where she just cooks whatever for you.  Some people may not like that, and if you have food allergies you're out of luck because they won't tell you anything.

Unfortunately, I waited too long to write this review and don't remember many details. However, we went having heard wonderful things, and were not disappointed. Highly recommended, worth the price, would gladly go again.

Alana's Food and Wine takes the upmost care in both atmosphere and food preparation. The kitchen is spotless and cleaned multiple times a day. Alana ensures that all products are local and organic. The cuisine is creative and changes daily. The employees are happy and enjoy their job. Alana's food and wine is a fine establishment with both character and heart.

Fantastic food.  Fun, friendly staff.  Nice, cozy atmosphere, great for dinner with a small group. Menu is eclectic, and everything I have eaten there has been wonderful.  Good wine and beer selection as well.

Great atmosphere! We started with the mussels appetizer and it was delicious and more then we could 1 guy and 4 girls could eat! I had the special of the day shrimp scampi and it was also delicious and more than i could eat! Everyone loved their meal!

If you didn't know spagio has a wine cellar side offering a different menu with some really yummy things and a way more casual atmosphere. If you'd like you can walk around and pick out your own wine or your beer from the coolers and then a server will come and assist you. I've always enjoyed it. There's ample seating including outdoor which is fun when the weather is good to watch the action on Grandview Avenue :-) but this time we went in just to look for a particular wine an Italian one we have tried in Canada they didn't actually have the wine but we're familiar with what we were talking about and we're totally willing to order it and much to my surprise they don't gouge you on the price they actually charge State minimum so if you want a good bottle of wine go here! Whether it's for home or to have in the restaurant
The food was great! The atmosphere and service were awesome! My wife and I had a great time, we will definitely go again.
Perfect service. My party liked their dishes, such as the lobster ravioli. I had the meatloaf.  It was ok. But the unobtrusive and always on-point service was the highlight.
The special chicken was amazing. We went back for it again. And the price is really good.

Found this spot on Google. The food was on point. The jerk chicken was mad good. Rice and peas was mad good. Living in the Bronx, it's hard to find a good Jamaican spot OT. It was noon, so the food was fresh... When I slide though OH, I'm coming back. Bless up...

I  absolutely love their food!!! The king fish my goodness!!!!! I love their food so much that I  decided them to  cater for an event that I am having. I called them to get some information and place a order, the woman who answered the phone was every rude and unprofessional. I said hi would like to talk to someone about catering please....”Ugh....oh my goodness...yes how can I help you” it’s unfortunate because I really wanted to use them.

DO NOT purchase the Curry chicken in a car of hungry kids! It's AMAZING!! Fortunately small pieces of the Beef patties held them over. They were crushed that I didn't by more!😆 I have to get here monthly. AMAZING!

Been to this place a couple times and the food is amazing! There is always a line to the door so expect to wait at least 30 minutes for your food, or call ahead. To me it’s well worth the wait. The mac and cheese is great, collard greens out of this world, and great jerk chicken. Big portions as well. The flavor is good to me and my boyfriend is Jamaican and says this food reminds him of home. It is more of a carry out place as they don’t have much seating but it would be awesome if they did and turned it into a more restaurant style.
Hey Zulu, man you have done some great work with the place... love it!!! Thanks for the stew fish it was delicious. Looking forward to my next visit brother.  See you soon!!!

What an incredible experience. Beautiful architecture, wonderful history and well preserved and detailed grounds. We had a great time. Parking was easy and affordable and everyone was friendly. This is a great tribute to Ohioans and Americans alike.
Beautiful architecture, definitely worth a visit. I especially enjoyed the free guided tours offered on weekdays on the hour. That made my day visit to Columbus from Florida doubly enjoyable.

There is a lot to do in the Ohio State Capitol inside and outside the Capitol Plaza building, which helps narrow down the scope before you visit. The State Capitol is home to Ohio's official business activities. A free guided tour is provided daily to provide an overview of the best history and design. If you choose to visit yourself, be sure to observe the large rotunda with thousands of marbles inside and visit the Museum Education Center. The Statehouse gift shop features unique gifts and artwork from Ohio artists. You will want to walk around the state capitol, observe statues, monuments and tribute to important VIPs and historic moments in Ohio.
The Ohio Statehouse is a magnificent work of patience and perseverance. The architecture is remarkable. The history is intriguing. The Ohio Statehouse is a place all Ohioans should visit often.
It's very beautiful place and I feel the peace in this place.

This museum is a GEM! Thoughtfully curated with every type of art you could desire to peruse. I especially enjoyed all the interactive stations. My friend and I colored like we were 12 again and sat and answered questions, learning things about one another. The black light exhibit is awesome (ask for the black 3D glasses) as is the texture room. Wonderful African-American exhibitions. I highly recommend an afternoon here.

This is a great place to bring kids, art lovers, and for students! I love the various rooms and themes they have. I love the art they have and especially enjoy the interactive pieces, which makes learning fun. The interactive pieces makes it engaging and interesting, for all ages.
It's amazing and really great to see local artists as well as wider known artists. There's various exhibits you can walk in and out of. There's also an area that people have their weddings and receptions in.
I love that they offer free admissions on Sundays! There's parking, but usually you have to pay.

Beautiful, well curated museum. Kid friendly! Anyone can visit for free on Sundays, although it tends to be their busiest day. For a bit of a quieter experience go on Thursday night. Entrance fee is only $5 between 5 and 9pm. There's also cool events to enjoy from time to time so make sure to look at the calendar before heading out.

I think they did a wonderful job with the museum. I love the "Join The Conversation" spots where people can respond the prompts and see what others have said.
They seem to be working very actively to highlight minority art, including lots of African American exhibits. Many of the information cards next to each piece contain not only relevant tidbits about the artist, but also questions to help you examine and think about the painting.

Loved my experience at the Columbus museum.  So much to see. As a adult I felt like a kid again. Also a great place for elementary age kids to enjoy. A lot to learn and the exhibits are exceptional.  I love the fact they have a hands on area for children as well. Even better its free every Sunday. It gets a little crowded so I would plan for a good 4-5 hours of being there if you want to see and read everything.  The staff is very helpful and clean restrooms.

This park is absolutely gorgeous in the summer. The fountain is great and is a great addition to the park. I love when it's warm and you can hear the fountain and people at the park. I especially love seeing the dogs run around and people hanging out. The gazebo is a great place to sit and enjoy the weather.
The only thing is parking, it is a bit rough because it's street parking and can fill up quite quickly! There's also a bunch of shopping and food places around the area, so you can explore a variety of businesses.

A spacious park that is pretty quiet when the are no events using it. It has a very photogenic atmosphere down by the pond and the gazebo. Most of the wildlife is used to people hanging around so if you move slowly you can get pretty close with your camera for photos.
Spent most day in this beautiful park today. Many doggies who were amazing. They all played and wore each other out. Owners were friendly and very chill. Overall always a fun experience.

A jewel of green in a rapidly changing city. Goodale Park is one of the oldest and largest public parks in Columbus, and boasts large, old tree stock, tennis and basketball courts, a playground, and horseshoe area (or cornhole - whichever you prefer).

Paths trace throughout the park and there is ample bike parking around the perimeter. Of special interest are the stone entry gates, as well as the water features in the area.

Goodale Park is also tended in part by the Friends of Goodale Park, who volunteer their time and energy to maintaining one of the best amenities in town.
Been here a few times. Lots of walking paths throughout the park. Nice pond and gazebo. Tennis. Basketball. Playground for the kids.

Beats the pants off of olive garden. But then again,  ketchup on lasagna noodles beats olive garden. It's a really cool place inside. There's a train car, and an elevator table and a few other cool places to eat. Not what you'd expect from a chain restaurant. Prices are very fair and service is always top notch. Ask for Jimmy if you can. He's so personable and doesn't just treat you like another table. Where else can you get spaghetti with meatballs, a piece of delicious sweet Italian sausage, and crispy garlic bread for only $14? Parking is a breeze and its laid out so that even when it's crowded, you're not right on top of people.

Used to love going here with my grandparents when I was young. The food tastes different now but the atmosphere is the same. My kids like it here because there is always something to look at and the bread is still really good.

Great place for larger group lunches during the work day or a neat place to have dinner on the weekend.  They accommodated our party of 10 for lunch, we were served in a timely manner and the food was great.   Ive also attended a retirement luncheon here with 50+ people and the experience was usual.   Ample servers assigned, food came out hot and was still great.

Lose yourself in this unique Italian restaurant... sample their sourdough bread with the amazing butter spread. Order some pasta to fill up on... and to top it off. A divine piece of Italian cream torte... I'm salivating just thinking about it! Or go for the more traditional cheesecake... ☆☆☆☆ definitely the flavor overload you were looking for!

The only thing good about this restaurant was the decor. It was very unique inside with a trolley car. It wasn't packed when we went so the service should be spot on. It wasn't as we all waited 15 min for drinks and I waited 30 additional min for my adult beverage... Food wasn't great either. My lasagna was just sauce and pasta with hardly any meat on it. Didn't really taste great either. It seemed like teenagers were running the place and they didn't seem like they wanted to be there. Will never go back... Had better Italian food at Angie's Italian restaurant in Barberton.
This is a small and beautiful park near the Susquehanna and Chenango rivers. The place is good for a picnic and would be nice rest from walking.
Beautiful little park at the confluence of the Susquehanna and Chenango rivers. The river walk is one of my favorite places in the city.
Very nice well-kept good for picnic or public get together
Not very big. History explained on a plaque. Nice for a rest from walking.
Scenic local park at the confluence of the Susquehanna and Chenango Rivers.

One of the best dinners I've experienced!  The food was superb, and the atmosphere was intimate with great service and wine selection.  I'm not a food expert and not particularly fond of French food but it was delicious!

We went there with our 12-year old about a month ago and it was spectacular. We eat out a lot and try to pick good restaurants wherever in the world we are, and this gem of a restaurant is right there at the top with some of the best we ever tried. The decor and the service are decent - nothing to be specially remembered, but the food is spectacular - truly a pleasure. All three of us agreed.

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.

I have visited the Annunciation Greek Orthodox Cathedral several times over the years; most often to attend the annual Greek Festival with its great variety of music, dancing, and food.

If you are not familiar with traditions of the Greek Orthodox Church, I recommend taking the cathedral tour at some point during the Greek Festival.

One nice thing about the Greek Festival is that you pay your admission fee once and then you are permitted to attend the festival for the rest of the weekend.
Great for weddings. Large weddings
Absolutely a beautiful place for a wedding!!
Wonderful location by Convention center

The Greek Orthodox Church*  most beautiful sight to see in Columbus. There is a wonderful Greekfest going on this weekend.   Went to there as a child, I can remember every fine detail.  Unforgettable.  The inside main area, the church is super big, so much that it made me dizzy.  Besides, thats where my familys time capsule is located.   My grandfather, who is now passed, he helped built this gorgeous place.  I look forward every year to going, sadly, I may not be able to afford it.  I love this place so much!  Its worth to experience it.

Really nice. 
Very helpful and caring people
Great volunteers make you feel so welcome
Friendly and welcoming to everyone.
Went to see a play about human trafficking

First Congregational Church is an "Open and Affirming" church within the United Church of Christ [UCC] denomination that fully welcomes LGBT people.

For longer than 150 years, First Congregational Church has been in the forefront of social justice change in central Ohio and beyond.

First Congregational Church also has a wonderful music program.

Love this place, no complaints. It's fun mixing and matching sauces. None of the meat we ordered was dry at all, which was a nice little surprise! Bit pricey, so I can't come here too often. I think my favorite was the pulled pork. Nice cozy interior, rustic feel.

This is a review of the Upper Arlington location for 4/10/19 at 4:20pm. The two women in the front need to work on their customer service skills. We arrived to pick up an online order. We stood at the registered with two female employees standing at the food window.....while they were getting another order together, neither bothered to even acknowledge us or say "we will be right with you". After 5 minutes they finally asked what we needed. Then as we were checking the order and mentioned that we were not sure everything was correct, the one stated, "it's all their" in a condescending tone.

Great BBQ but the menu is confusing when trying to place an order. I realize that they are playing to the customers that are repeat and know the operation but it is very hard for a newbie to make a decision when ordering their meal up front. Good example is the difference between a lunch sandwich and a regular.
With almost 1000 reviews they have to be doing something right. Great food, outstanding atmosphere. Employees are always great to customers. 5 stars all day!
It's okay. Decent BBQ, sauces are good. Service is poor. Good for a BBQ fix, but not for anybody serious about their cue

I've enjoyed many good meals at the Hickory house and Aspen. They have fantastic BBQ and are very reasonably priced.  Today I had breakfast at the HH for the first time.  They  did not disappoint.   I had the Chicken Fried Chicken and my wife had the Breakfast Burrito.   Both were great.  Ample portions, and again, reasonably price.   Enjoy Western Lodge Style atmosphere, great service, and food.

I can't count a time when this place isn't busy. Even though it's a crowded place the servers, and cooks do an excellent job at making the visits pleasant. There's a great selection of steaks, burgers, ribs, and other assorted barbecue styled food. The only reason I don't give it a five star rating is because of how crowded it usually is, but that's probably because the food is so good. Other than that, I'd say it's an excellent place to get a great bite to eat in Aspen at an affordable price.

Got the "Beast" pulled pork. Huge serving of great meat. The pork alone was a bit lacking in flavor, but extremely well made and the specialty bbq sauces were great. 

Our seat was near the door and we were bumped by nearly everyone that walked by whole sitting at an uncomfortable tall metal table. This place should have remodeled during the road construction last year. The layout is terrible. The atmosphere is great, but don't plan on moving around in this cramped place.

This restaurant claims to have the best ribs in the entire state of Colorado. Wife and I shared a rack of baby backs.   They are good but I've had better on the front range.  For the money this is a good BBQ place but I won't be coming back if I can help it.
Wonderful place! Our waitress remembered all the orders for all 10 of us - very impressive. Great ribs!!

This was our first time and wow, super impressed! Kaylee was our waitress and she is one of those rare individuals who exude happiness. Prices were high but when you figure on the double portion size, not bad at all. A must do for those visiting Branson and a will do over and over for locals.  Ask to be seated in Kaylee's section, she is the best!

I love this place! They offer fun bibs with fun comments on them for people ordering the big buckets. They gave my date one, too, saying they didn't want her to feel left out. The crab legs that I ordered were delicious and the cooked veggies tasted amazing. I had so much food that I had plenty to eat as a midnight snack later.

I am a huge fan of crab so I like to go to Joe's Crab Shack whenever I am in the area! I always get the steam pots and I am never disappointed! You get a nice variety of crab legs, potatoes, shrimp, sausage and corn. They also have the restuarant placed right by the lake so the views are fantastic. I will definitely be back again!

The food was great. Our waitress, Breeana, was hopping busy but still had time to stop and grab any items we requested. Something huge for me, they have a gluten free menu! There were no issues with the menu request either. (Not everyone is kind when you have to request something gluten free.) My daughter absolutely loved "painting" her dessert. My other daughter even got full and had to take food home. (Something rare for a growing girl like her!) We hope to go back on our next trip to Branson.

For the price the food wasn't great, it was more along the lines of captain d's or long john silvers. The drinks were mostly just a mix without any alcohol, should have been top shelf for the size and price. Disappointed that we spent $100 for a dinner for two and could have had a similar experience at a fast food place. We even were seated at a table in a corner with baby seats blocking the view which would have been the only good thing about the place. I feel like we wasted our money and the trip to Branson for dinner.

This place was phenomenal they have a buffet there that is so good and very authentic! we had the most entertaining guy playing the accordion for us it was something special if I can find my pictures I will definitely post a picture! oh my gosh I may have these phenomenal desserts also let me tell you the cream puffs were like gigantic and so many different flavors. Really good service too servers are so friendly and nice. The next time I'm in the Columbus area I'm definitely going to go there again! I highly recommend this place for the food, the atmosphere, and the fun!!!

The food at Schmidt's is not my favorite. I'm not a huge fan of German food in general, and I like the way Wurst und Bier serves up schnitzel, my favorite German dish, better than Schmidt's does. Still, if you are a fan of German food, or just a fan of unique, destination dining, you owe it to yourself to visit Schmidt's. This place attracts lots of tourists, but it is also a local favorite. German Village is a beautiful, historic Columbus neighborhood, and Schmidt's is a deserving anchor and part of its charm. Although most of the menu just isn't my cup of tea, one huge exception to this is the famous Schmidt's cream puff. All other cream puff pale in comparison. I've been known to hunt down one of Schmidt's food trucks visiting my neighborhood just to get a cream puff. They are so good!

We stopped here for lunch while in Columbus for an overnight stay. The food and ambiance were amazing. The sausages were flavorful and on point. The sides were excellent. The red cabbage and German potato salad were well flavored and balanced, not too sweet. My wife had a chicken dish with a basil cream sauce that was outstanding. 
You must get one of the enormous cream puffs. Perfect end to our meal. 
If ever in Columbus, this is a must for great German food.

We were recommended by locals to visit this place and was very pleased! The restaurant actually looks like something out of a Christmas village, so wonderful & quaint! Once inside, we were greeted with a large glass case of their famous cream puffs the size of softballs, along with various pastries of German chocolate cake, French silk pies and more. Although the restaurant was crowded, we were seated almost immediately. Since it was our first time there, we opted for the buffet. There were various types of German sausages, pastas, potato salads, 1 type of soup, rolls, etc. Everything we tried was exceptional! My husband & I ordered their hot buttered rum which was absolutely delicious. Service was wonderful! Overall, I can see why this place came highly recommended. Wonderful food, ambiance & service! Just sad we can't take this restaurant home with us lol

Hadn't been here in 10+ yrs, due to bad service & horrible buffet bar that day. Wanted to give it another try. Can't say it was fantastic, seeing how after we had our salads, went back to buffet for the main meal, come back to table to find it had been totally cleared off & apparently reset for new customers. Wow! Had to wait for new drinks & place settings while the food cooled.  Otherwise, food wasn't bad, but was it worth the $16 a person for buffet? Couldn't resist the pies though as take home option. But seriously, $50 (w tip) for 2 people??? The buffet isn't worth THAT much!! Another 10 yrs, me might try it again! Maybe...

They have a variety of dishes to meet your dietary and budget needs. Check out their specials for an even better deal. Pick-up is pretty fast, but dining in takes some time. I love the decor and the art they display for local artists. You can tell they have a great sense of community and service!
This place used to be great. Now... not so much. Here's a photo of the amount of lamb in their new wrap. Enjoy your several mouthfuls of onion, then a little cube of lamb, then more bites of onion...
Loved it. Went in for their Valentine's special and the food was amazing. The staff were super nice and helpful.

You should be one of my favorite places it is been in Decline since the owner sold it a couple years ago. Still great food just slower service and not really a great manager who knows how to run the place. Possibly there's no manager anymore. Again I  emphasize still great food
Every time I come here the food and service are stellar.  The spicy cauliflower is to die for and always remember to get an extra side of hit sauce!

They Lie to me NO Vegan Option & Waiting  There for Nothing waste of time at the Table. I Did NOT Like What Was on The Menu & it was Disgusting. So I left quick. I Did not want to be Seen There Either. Because I'm kinda famous. Definitely Not My Type Of Place.

I am vegan and one of my friends who went with me eats halal (my friend enjoyed the lamb). We loved the food and the experience so much that we came back the next night also. The staff and owners are very nice. Next time I am back in Albuquerque I will eat here again.

My favorite Indian food lunch buffet here in Albuquerque.  We make it a point to go meet at least once a month with our friends.  They have all the great stuff you'd expect at a Indian food buffet and they do a great job at all of it.  It's typically bustling and busy at lunch, but with several dining areas and attentive polite staff that are constantly on top of everything, it's always a pleasurable experience.

First time coming here, and first time eating Indian food, and I have to say that I loved it! The location is pretty old and might be in need for an update, but they make up for it with the great food. I went for lunch, and they have their buffet, which makes it really easy to get a sample of their offerings
Always wonderful!  Have been a patron for years, and it's always a good bet.  Had the baked eggplant and lamb meatballs.....great!  Always have an appetizer.
